WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.000
The Jackson family are on holiday in Turkey.

00:04.000 --> 00:08.000
They're staying at a big hotel in Istanbul.

00:08.000 --> 00:16.000
Mark, 13, his sister Fay, 12, and their parents like Turkey.

00:16.000 --> 00:21.000
It's beautiful, the weather's hot, and the food's good.

00:21.000 --> 00:24.000
There's a lot to see, too.

00:24.000 --> 00:28.000
Today, they're visiting the city of Troy.

00:29.000 --> 00:31.000
It's 9 o'clock in the morning.

00:31.000 --> 00:36.000
They're getting on a bus in front of their hotel.

00:38.000 --> 00:41.000
There are 40 people on the bus.

00:41.000 --> 00:47.000
They come from Britain, America, France, Italy, and Holland.

00:53.000 --> 00:56.000
At Troy, they all have lunch.

00:56.000 --> 00:59.000
Then they start to look at the old city.

00:59.000 --> 01:02.000
It's a very hot day.

01:02.000 --> 01:07.000
After an hour, Mark sits under a tree.

01:07.000 --> 01:10.000
I'm going to stop here for a moment.

01:10.000 --> 01:12.000
He tells Fay.

01:12.000 --> 01:16.000
Okay, she answers.

01:16.000 --> 01:19.000
Then Mark sees something on the ground.

01:19.000 --> 01:21.000
What's that?

01:21.000 --> 01:23.000
He thinks.

01:23.000 --> 01:26.000
It's a flat, yellow stone.

01:26.000 --> 01:28.000
Mark picks it up.

01:28.000 --> 01:32.000
Then he starts to clean it with his hands.

01:32.000 --> 01:37.000
But I know this stone, he thinks.

01:37.000 --> 01:40.000
It comes from... from...

01:40.000 --> 01:44.000
Suddenly, there's a white light in his eyes.

01:44.000 --> 01:46.000
Mark closes them.

01:46.000 --> 01:48.000
The light's strong.

01:48.000 --> 01:52.000
Now there's a loud wind in his ears.

01:52.000 --> 01:56.000
He can't hear or see anything.

01:56.000 --> 01:58.000
What's happening?

01:58.000 --> 02:00.000
He thinks.

02:00.000 --> 02:05.000
Ten seconds later, the light and the wind stop.

02:05.000 --> 02:08.000
Mark opens his eyes.

02:08.000 --> 02:10.000
He's standing on a beach.

02:10.000 --> 02:14.000
He can see hundreds of ships and men.

02:14.000 --> 02:19.000
Behind him, there's a beautiful city with high walls.

02:19.000 --> 02:21.000
Where am I?

02:21.000 --> 02:23.000
He thinks.

02:23.000 --> 02:25.000
Where's my family?

02:25.000 --> 02:29.000
He puts the yellow stone in his pocket.

02:29.000 --> 02:32.000
Then one of the men says to him,

02:32.000 --> 02:35.000
Boy, come here.

02:35.000 --> 02:37.000
Me?

02:37.000 --> 02:42.000
Mark walks across the beach to a long black ship.

02:42.000 --> 02:44.000
Carry this.

02:44.000 --> 02:46.000
The man says.

02:46.000 --> 02:49.000
He gives Mark a lot of wood.

02:49.000 --> 02:51.000
Then he gets off the ship.

02:51.000 --> 02:54.000
Follow me, he says.

02:54.000 --> 02:57.000
Mark follows him.

02:57.000 --> 03:02.000
The man's very tall and has a short brown beard.

03:02.000 --> 03:05.000
I don't know your face, he says.

03:05.000 --> 03:08.000
Are you new here?

03:08.000 --> 03:11.000
Yes, Mark answers.

03:11.000 --> 03:15.000
That's right, I'm new here.

03:15.000 --> 03:20.000
My name's Andros, says the man.

03:20.000 --> 03:24.000
He and Mark walk for another ten minutes.

03:24.000 --> 03:27.000
Then they climb a small hill.

03:27.000 --> 03:30.000
At the top, Mark stops.

03:30.000 --> 03:35.000
There, in front of them, is a big wooden horse.

03:35.000 --> 03:39.000
Andros sees Mark's face and smiles.

03:39.000 --> 03:43.000
Well, what do you think of it?

03:43.000 --> 03:45.000
He asks.

03:45.000 --> 03:47.000
Mark doesn't answer.

03:47.000 --> 03:49.000
And Andros says,

03:49.000 --> 03:55.000
This horse is going to win the war for us Greeks.

03:55.000 --> 03:57.000
They walk down the hill.

03:57.000 --> 04:01.000
There are a lot of men working under the horse.

04:01.000 --> 04:04.000
One of them talks to Andros.

04:04.000 --> 04:07.000
There's a problem, he says.

04:07.000 --> 04:11.000
We can't find a stone for the second eye.

04:11.000 --> 04:15.000
We must find one before tomorrow.

04:15.000 --> 04:19.000
Mark looks at the horse's one bright eye.

04:19.000 --> 04:23.000
Then he remembers the stone in his pocket.

04:23.000 --> 04:25.000
Wait, he says.

04:25.000 --> 04:28.000
I think I can help you.

04:28.000 --> 04:32.000
He takes the stone out of his pocket.

04:32.000 --> 04:33.000
But how?

04:33.000 --> 04:35.000
Says Andros.

04:35.000 --> 04:38.000
The man smiles.

04:38.000 --> 04:41.000
That's it. That's it.

04:41.000 --> 04:44.000
He looks at Mark.

04:44.000 --> 04:47.000
What's your name, boy?

04:47.000 --> 04:49.000
Mark tells him.

04:49.000 --> 04:52.000
He's new here, says Andros.

04:52.000 --> 04:54.000
Ah!

04:54.000 --> 04:57.000
The man's very happy.

04:57.000 --> 05:01.000
Well, we must thank him.

05:01.000 --> 05:07.000
I know you can come with us in the horse tomorrow night.

05:07.000 --> 05:10.000
Mark's mouth opens.

05:10.000 --> 05:13.000
Me?

05:13.000 --> 05:18.000
That evening, Mark sits near a big fire on the beach.

05:18.000 --> 05:21.000
There's an old woman beside him.

05:21.000 --> 05:25.000
Her name is Anna, and she's a cook.

05:25.000 --> 05:28.000
She tells Mark lots of stories.

05:28.000 --> 05:36.000
Stories about Greece, the war, and the beautiful princess, Helen.

05:37.000 --> 05:40.000
In the end, she goes to bed.

05:40.000 --> 05:42.000
Goodbye, boy.

05:42.000 --> 05:44.000
She says.

05:44.000 --> 05:47.000
Come and see me again one day.

05:47.000 --> 05:51.000
Come and see me again.

05:51.000 --> 05:55.000
Next morning, the horse is ready.

05:55.000 --> 05:58.000
Greek soldiers pull it to the gates of Troy.

05:58.000 --> 06:01.000
Then they leave it there.

06:01.000 --> 06:05.000
Inside the horse, there are 40 Greeks.

06:05.000 --> 06:10.000
They wait all afternoon under the hot yellow sun.

06:10.000 --> 06:13.000
Mark's sitting in the horse's head.

06:13.000 --> 06:15.000
What happens now?

06:15.000 --> 06:17.000
He thinks.

06:17.000 --> 06:21.000
Suddenly, the gates open.

06:27.000 --> 06:30.000
Trojan soldiers walk out.

06:30.000 --> 06:34.000
They pull the horse inside and shut the gates again.

06:36.000 --> 06:39.000
Mark can hear the Trojans.

06:39.000 --> 06:43.000
Why are the Greeks giving us this horse?

06:43.000 --> 06:45.000
Asks one.

06:45.000 --> 06:48.000
Do you think they want to end the war?

06:48.000 --> 06:51.000
Yes. Look.

06:51.000 --> 06:54.000
Says a soldier on top of the city walls.

06:54.000 --> 06:57.000
Their ships are leaving.

06:57.000 --> 07:04.000
After that, the Trojans eat, sing, and dance all evening.

07:06.000 --> 07:11.000
Then they go to bed very late, and Troy is quiet.

07:11.000 --> 07:18.000
At that moment, the Greeks climb out of the horse.

07:18.000 --> 07:22.000
Four men go to the gates and open them.

07:22.000 --> 07:27.000
A minute later, there are thousands of Greek soldiers in the city.

07:27.000 --> 07:31.000
They and their ships are back.

07:31.000 --> 07:35.000
They run from one building to another.

07:35.000 --> 07:39.000
In five minutes, Troy is on fire.

07:39.000 --> 07:42.000
Mark watches all this.

07:42.000 --> 07:46.000
Suddenly, he sees a beautiful woman.

07:46.000 --> 07:49.000
She's running along the city walls.

07:49.000 --> 07:52.000
It's Helen, he thinks.

07:52.000 --> 07:56.000
Helen of Troy.

07:56.000 --> 07:59.000
At that moment, Andros says,

07:59.000 --> 08:01.000
Follow me, boy.

08:01.000 --> 08:05.000
He runs down a small street very fast.

08:05.000 --> 08:10.000
Mark follows, but the streets full of smoke.

08:10.000 --> 08:14.000
After a minute, he can't see anything.

08:14.000 --> 08:17.000
Andros, he says,

08:17.000 --> 08:19.000
Where are you?

08:19.000 --> 08:25.000
Then suddenly, two Trojans with swords come out of the smoke.

08:25.000 --> 08:27.000
Mark looks at them.

08:27.000 --> 08:29.000
Please don't kill me.

08:29.000 --> 08:32.000
He says, don't kill me.

08:32.000 --> 08:35.000
Please.

08:35.000 --> 08:40.000
Mark, Mark, it's four o'clock.

08:40.000 --> 08:43.000
The bus is leaving in a minute.

08:43.000 --> 08:47.000
Fay is looking down at Mark.

08:47.000 --> 08:51.000
After a moment, he suddenly wakes up.

08:51.000 --> 08:53.000
What?

08:53.000 --> 08:55.000
He asks.

08:55.000 --> 08:57.000
The bus is leaving.

08:57.000 --> 08:59.000
Fay says again.

08:59.000 --> 09:01.000
Then she asks,

09:01.000 --> 09:03.000
Are you okay?

09:03.000 --> 09:05.000
Your face is white.

09:05.000 --> 09:08.000
And what's that dirty stone?

09:08.000 --> 09:12.000
Mark looks at the yellow stone in his hand.

09:12.000 --> 09:13.000
This?

09:13.000 --> 09:16.000
Oh, it's nothing.

09:16.000 --> 09:18.000
He says.

09:18.000 --> 09:20.000
Mark stands up.

09:20.000 --> 09:23.000
He sees an old woman.

09:23.000 --> 09:28.000
She has lots of small wooden horses in a basket.

09:28.000 --> 09:30.000
Do you want one boy?

09:30.000 --> 09:32.000
She asks.

09:32.000 --> 09:35.000
Yes, why not?

09:35.000 --> 09:39.000
Mark buys a horse and looks at the woman.

09:39.000 --> 09:43.000
No, it can't be.

09:43.000 --> 09:44.000
He thinks.

09:44.000 --> 09:47.000
He walks to the bus.

09:47.000 --> 09:51.000
Behind him, the old woman smiles.

09:51.000 --> 09:53.000
Goodbye, boy.

09:53.000 --> 09:55.000
She says.

09:55.000 --> 09:58.000
Come and see me again one day.

09:58.000 --> 10:01.000
Come and see me again.

